The paper discusses the use of tensor regression networks for efficient compression of model parameters in multilayer perceptrons (MLP) and evaluates the performance on CIFAR-10 dataset using state-of-the-art deep convolutional models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
